
[1]hydroscope

   HY'DROSCOPE, n. [Gr. water, and to view.] A kind of water clock,or
   instrument used anciently for measuring time, consisting of a
   cylindrical tube, conical at the bottom, perforated at the vertex, and
   the whole tube graduated.
